We Are Not Ourselves documents the American moment at the close of a global war, reminding us of the powers of love, family bonds, and the never-ending pursuit for a better life. Chad Harbach ( The Art of Fielding ) has called Thomas's work as "powerfully moving" and was praised by Joshua Ferris ( Then We Came To The End ) as a "masterwork" of contemporary fiction. Matthew Thomas was born in the Bronx and grew up in Queens. A graduate of the University of Chicago, he has an MA from the Writing Seminars at Johns Hopkins University and an MFA from the University of California, Irvine, where he received the Graduate Essay Award. He lives with his wife and twin children in New Jersey.      LOCATION CHANGE!
